===Etymology===
厂 (to announce) + 一 + 口 (a mouth). It represents the powerful queue gives orders.

===Han character===
{{Han char|rn=30|rad=口|as=03|sn=6|four=7226<sub>1</sub>|canj=竹一口 (HMR)|ids=⿸[[𠂋]][[口]]}}

# [[queen]], [[empress]], [[sovereign]] (Simplified and Traditional)
# [[after]], [[following]], [[behind]] ''(Simplified only)''

This character is present in both Traditional and Simplified Chinese. However, it only means "after" or "behind" when it is simplified due to the merging of characters 后 and [[後]] in Simplified Chinese. The latter is used to represent "after" in Traditional Chinese.

